A3: Closed Ecological Life Support Systems (CELSS): State of the Art

System Components & Recycling Targets

Water Recovery:

· Target: >98% closure
· ISS System: Water processor assembly (WPA) + urine processor (UPA)
  · Recovery: 93% from urine, 98% from humidity
  · Technologies: Distillation, catalytic oxidation, ion exchange
· Next Generation: Forward osmosis, membrane distillation
· Biological: Plant transpiration (~99% pure water)

Atmosphere Revitalization:

· CO₂ removal: 1 kg/person/day
· Current: CO₂ → CH₄ (Sabatier) or LiOH canisters
· Advanced: 4BIO-MELiSSA loop (microalgae + higher plants)
  · Spirulina: 1.8 kg O₂/kg biomass, absorbs 2.4 kg CO₂

Food Production:

· Caloric requirement: 2800 kcal/person/day
· Current yield: 20-30 g edible biomass/kWh (LED optimized)
· Best candidates:
  · Sweet potato: 5.2 kcal/cm²/day
  · Quinoa: Complete protein, high yield
  · Duckweed: 10× faster growth than soy, 45% protein

Mass Balance for 4-Person Mars Habitat

Component Daily Requirement System Mass Power (kW)
Oxygen 2.5 kg 200 kg (storage) 0.5
Water 20 kg 500 kg (recycler) 1.2
Food 5 kg 2000 kg (hydroponics) 4.0
Waste Processing 2 kg 300 kg 0.8
Total 29.5 kg 3000 kg 6.5 kW

Closure Rates after 5 Years:

· Oxygen: 99.8%
· Water: 98.5%
· Food: 85% (supplements needed)
· Waste: 95% conversion to fertilizer

